{"type":"message","id":"e06afb2a","parentId":"4ef73877","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:12:44.345Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Constructing a Benchmark Script**\n\nI'm now focused on the benchmark script, specifically `tests/perf/rust_vs_python.py`. The plan is a direct comparison between Python's native execution and calling a Rust extension. My aim is to simulate or gracefully skip the Rust part if compilation or calling fails, ensuring the benchmark runs smoothly.\n\n\n**Designing the Benchmark Script**\n\nI'm zeroing in on the script's core functionality. I'll include an import attempt of the Rust module, and if that fails, I'll log \"N/A\" for the Rust component's performance. The script will be designed to run regardless of Rust's build status, providing a useful comparison either way. I am also checking how to integrate http/2 into the benchmarks.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771179164340_112","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import time\nimport timeit\nimport asyncio\nimport httpx\nimport sys\nimport os\n\n# Try to import the rust core module if available\ntry:\n    import rust_core\nexcept ImportError:\n    rust_core = None\n\ndef python_heavy_computation(n):\n    \"\"\"Simulate heavy computation in Python.\"\"\"\n    result = 0\n    for i in range(n):\n        result += i * i\n    return result\n\ndef run_benchmark():\n    n = 1_000_000\n    \n    # Python Benchmark\n    start_py = time.perf_counter()\n    python_heavy_computation(n)\n    end_py = time.perf_counter()\n    py_duration = (end_py - start_py) * 1000\n    \n    print(f\"Python Computation: {py_duration:.4f} ms\")\n\n    # Rust Benchmark\n    rs_duration = 0\n    if rust_core and hasattr(rust_core, 'heavy_computation'):\n        start_rs = time.perf_counter()\n        rust_core.heavy_computation(n)\n        end_rs = time.perf_counter()\n        rs_duration = (end_rs - start_rs) * 1000\n        print(f\"Rust Computation: {rs_duration:.4f} ms\")\n    else:\n        print(\"Rust module not available or function missing. Skipping Rust benchmark.\")\n        rs_duration = -1 # Indicate failure/missing\n\n    return py_duration, rs_duration\n\nasync def check_http2():\n    \"\"\"Check if HTTP/2 is supported/enabled.\"\"\"\n    # This is a simplified check. In a real scenario, we'd hit an endpoint that supports H2.\n    # Here we check if the client *can* do HTTP/2.\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(http2=True) as client:\n        return client.http2\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    print(\"Running Rust vs Python Benchmark...\")\n    py_time, rs_time = run_benchmark()\n    \n    print(\"\\nChecking HTTP/2 Capability...\")\n    http2_enabled = asyncio.run(check_http2())\n    print(f\"HTTP/2 Enabled: {http2_enabled}\")\n    \n    # Simple JSON output for the main script to parse\n    import json\n    results = {\n        \"python_avg\": py_time,\n        \"rust_avg\": rs_time,\n        \"http2_enabled\": http2_enabled\n    }\n    print(\"__JSON_START__\")\n    print(json.dumps(results))\n    print(\"__JSON_END__\")\n","file_path":"tests/perf/rust_vs_python.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":115769,"output":968,"cacheRead":114467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116737,"cost":{"input":0.231538,"output":0.011616,"cacheRead":0.0228934,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.2660474}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771179150698}}
