{"type":"message","id":"d81dc443","parentId":"4ce3ae6c","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:12:54.837Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing Autonomous Backlog**\n\nI'm now diving into the `AUTONOMOUS_BACKLOG.md` file. My immediate goal is to identify areas for improvement. I'm focusing on finding instances of legacy `threading` that might benefit from `multiprocessing`. I'll also be searching for missing docstrings, and keeping an eye out for any weak error handling.\n\n\n**Analyzing the Documentation Scan**\n\nI'm making progress. I've switched gears and am now planning the `scan_backlog.py` script. The intent is to automate the identification of the issues I flagged earlier. It will be much more efficient to execute everything through the script than through a series of greps. Creating the initial draft now.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771179174828_113","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import os\nimport re\n\ndef scan_files(root_dir):\n    backlog = []\n    \n    for root, dirs, files in os.walk(root_dir):\n        if \"__pycache__\" in dirs:\n            dirs.remove(\"__pycache__\")\n            \n        for file in files:\n            if file.endswith(\".py\"):\n                path = os.path.join(root, file)\n                try:\n                    with open(path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n                        lines = f.readlines()\n                        \n                    content = \"\".join(lines)\n                    \n                    # Check for threading import\n                    if \"import threading\" in content or \"from threading import\" in content:\n                        backlog.append(f\"- **[HIGH]** Legacy `threading` usage in `{path}`. Consider migrating to `multiprocessing` for CPU-bound tasks.\")\n                        \n                    # Check for missing docstrings\n                    for i, line in enumerate(lines):\n                        if line.strip().startswith(\"def \"):\n                            func_name = line.split(\"def \")[1].split(\"(\")[0]\n                            # Look ahead for docstring\n                            has_docstring = False\n                            for j in range(i + 1, min(i + 5, len(lines))):\n                                if '\"\"\"' in lines[j] or \"'''\" in lines[j]:\n                                    has_docstring = True\n                                    break\n                            if not has_docstring:\n                                backlog.append(f\"- **[LOW]** Missing docstring for `{func_name}` in `{path}`.\")\n                                \n                    # Check for weak error handling (bare except)\n                    if \"except:\" in content: # broad except\n                         backlog.append(f\"- **[MED]** Weak error handling (bare `except:`) in `{path}`.\")\n                         \n                except Exception as e:\n                    # Skip files that can't be read (binary, etc.)\n                    continue\n                    \n    return backlog\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    backlog_items = scan_files(\"src\")\n    \n    # Save to docs/AUTONOMOUS_BACKLOG.md\n    with open(\"docs/AUTONOMOUS_BACKLOG.md\", \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        f.write(\"# Autonomous Backlog\\n\\n\")\n        if backlog_items:\n            for item in backlog_items:\n                f.write(item + \"\\n\")\n        else:\n            f.write(\"No backlog items found.\\n\")\n            \n    print(f\"Scanned {len(backlog_items)} items.\")\n","file_path":"scan_backlog.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":116578,"output":728,"cacheRead":114262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117306,"cost":{"input":0.233156,"output":0.008736,"cacheRead":0.022852400000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.2647444}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771179164363}}
