{"type":"message","id":"7a508e1e","parentId":"64572cf8","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:13:47.185Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reflecting on the Report**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI'm revisiting `run_operation.py` now. The primary issue is encoding when printing the report. I'm considering several solutions. One involves manually encoding to UTF-8 before decoding, but a quicker fix is to display `[FAIL]` instead of the unicode \"❌\". It's a trade-off between detail and simplicity.\n\n\n**Considering Core Changes**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nMy focus is shifting to `src/core/utils.py`. The initial plan was to handle Unicode directly in `run_operation.py`, but simplifying the output in `utils.py` seems more efficient. I'm exploring safer character replacements to ensure cross-platform compatibility, particularly for Windows environments, thus streamlining console output significantly. This should bypass the encoding issues directly.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771179227177_117","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/utils.py","newText":"    report.append(\"\\n## 2. HTTP/2 Status\")\n    status_icon = \"[OK]\" if http2_status else \"[FAIL]\"\n    report.append(f\"- **HTTP/2 Enabled:** {status_icon}\")","oldText":"    report.append(\"\\n## 2. HTTP/2 Status\")\n    status_icon = \"✅\" if http2_status else \"❌\"\n    report.append(f\"- **HTTP/2 Enabled:** {status_icon}\")"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":121636,"output":313,"cacheRead":118040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121949,"cost":{"input":0.243272,"output":0.0037560000000000002,"cacheRead":0.023608,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.270636}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771179219752}}
